FBIS3-10003 "drlat040_a_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-040 Document Type:Daily Report 1 March 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba General Colome Ibarra Issues Minint Forum Guidelines FL2502154594 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1200 GMT 25 Feb 94 FL2502154594 Havana Radio Progreso Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] The widespread implementation of solutions to problems is an Interior Ministry [Minint] priority in 1994 in preparation for the Ninth Science and Technology Forum. The guidelines issued by Army Corps General Abelardo Colome Ibarra, a member of the Politburo and head of the Minint, calls for increasing the number of proposals to promote efficiency in defense tasks and help improve operational response time, as well as promote favorable welfare conditions for the troops.
